<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-435-452  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 435 452.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  July 10 1989 n323 p39(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Silicon Glen leads way. (Scottish computer industry expands)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Scotland's computer industry is finally becoming a driving forcein its own right, after years of competing with London's industry.andO;Scotland's Silicon Glen includes more than 500 electronicmanufacturers and software development companies, and is home to anumber of American computer manufacturers, dealers anddistributors.andP;  Some American companies prefer to be in Scotlandbecause it is a cost-effective alternative to establishingoperations in England.andP;  Transportation is less congested and realestate is not as expensive.andP;  The government has encouraged foreigninvestment because of Scotland's high unemployment rate.andP;  However,some company executives feel a company must have strong operationsin England as well as in Scotland to be successful in the UnitedKingdom.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ScotlandComputer IndustryGrowthFacility LocationCompetitionCost Reduction.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Scotland - Scotland's computer industry. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>